The toll from Hurricane Agatha climbed to at least 10 dead and around 20 missing in southern Mexico, where heavy rains triggered landslides and flooding, local officials said Tuesday. "Right now we're at around 20 people missing, most of them are in the upper mountains," Oaxaca State Governor Alejandro Murat told Radio Formula, adding that the "10 who lost their lives were unfortunately preliminarily reported by local authorities." (Cover: Rain falls during the arrival of Hurricane Agatha in Huatulco, Oaxaca State, Mexico, May 30, 2022. /CFP)